// Shared tsconfig base for every task package's tsconfig.json (issue #409).
// Mirrors the Tasks/eslint.base.mjs factory pattern: a single source of truth
// for the compilerOptions duplicated identically across all 11 tasks.
//
// NOTE: "include" is deliberately NOT here. TypeScript resolves a config's
// "include"/"exclude"/"files" paths relative to the file that DECLARES them,
// not the file that extends it (confirmed via the TypeScript docs and a live
// empirical test: an "include" here would resolve to Tasks/src/**/*, which
// doesn't exist for any task, and every task's build would fail with
// TS18003 "No inputs were found"). Each task's own tsconfig.json keeps its
// "include": ["src/**/*"] for this reason.
//
// "target" is also deliberately NOT here, since it's the one setting that
// genuinely differs (TerraformTaskV5 uses ES2020; every other task uses ES6)
// -- each task's tsconfig.json sets it explicitly as a per-task override.
{
    "compilerOptions": {
        "module": "commonjs",
        "skipLibCheck": true,
        "strict": true,
        "noImplicitReturns": true,
        "noFallthroughCasesInSwitch": true
    }
}
